"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64810","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-07","<p> </p><p>Up until September 2013, UK Aid has supported over 6.4 million children in primary and lower secondary school, of which 3.1 million were girls, through our bilateral programmes. Of these, 4.2 million were in Sub-Saharan Africa and 2.1 million children were in South Asia. These figures are the latest available, and are reported in the DFID Annual Report and Accounts 2012/13.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-07-07T16:36:52.5142926Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64810/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64810/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64810/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-30","Developing Countries: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many children received schooling as a direct result of UK aid in (a) sub-Saharan Africa and (b) South Asia in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","202969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64811","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-07","<p> </p><p>DFID currently sits on the board of 28 multilateral organisations to which it gives core funding, sometimes representing the UK alone and sometimes also representing a constituency (group of donor members). DFID either attended, or was represented by a member of their constituency at, all Board meetings in the last 12 months.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-07-07T16:37:42.9392532Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64811/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64811/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64811/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-30","International Organisations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, on how many boards of multilateral organisations representatives from her Department sit; and how many meetings of each board such representatives of has not attended in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","202983"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64812","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-07","<p> </p><p>Her Majesty's Government will be represented at the conference. We do not routinely confirm attendance in advance.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-07-07T16:38:14.951471Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64812/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64812/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64812/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-30","AIDS: Conferences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, who will represent her Department at the upcoming International Aids Conference.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","202984"
