14-06-27","Higher Education: York","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many UCAS applications there were to (a) the University of York and (b) University of York St John in 2008-09 and in each year since then.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","202886"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64493","Department for Education","false","2014-07-08","<p>A co-educational school adopting a policy of separation on the basis of sex, which treated girls less favourably than boys (or vice versa), would be acting unlawfully under the Equality Act 2010. The Department for Education has issued advice to schools on the application of the Equality Act 2010:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/equality-act-2010-advice-for-schools" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/equality-act-2010-advice-for-schools</a></p><p>As this guidance states, it is possible to justify separate classes in exceptional circumstances, for example in delivering elements of sex and relationship education, or for PE. In all other cases, the Department expects co-educational schools to teach boys and girls in mixed classes and not to treat them differently because of their gender.</p><p> </p><p>Inspectors take into account guidance issued to schools by the Department, including the existing guidance on the Equality Act 2010. We would expect them to question a school about any segregation of pupils by gender to ensure that this is only taking place in exceptional circumstances as outlined by the Equality Act.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-07-08T10:10:24.5472136Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64493/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64493/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64493/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-27","Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, under what circumstances gender segregation of boys and girls in the classroom is permitted in schools; and if he will issue revised guidance on this matter to Ofsted.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","202912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64494","Department for Education","false","2014-07-07","<p>It is for the governing body of each school to set their own policies on school uniform and other matters of appearance. The Department for Education's guidance to schools on school uniform recommends that, once this policy is decided, the governing body should describe its uniform or appearance policy clearly and ensure that parents are informed.</p><p> </p><p>The uniform guidance reminds schools of their need to have full regard to their obligations under equalities law when setting and enforcing their school uniform policy. It also recommends that the governing body considers carefully any reasonable requests to vary their uniform policy to accommodate individual pupils' beliefs.</p><p> </p><p>The school uniform guidance is available at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-uniform" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-uniform</a>.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-07-07T11:45:41.1170814Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64494/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64494/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64494/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-27","Schools: Uniforms","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what guidance he gives to schools on steps they should take to inform students of their right to wear or not to wear religious clothing.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","202911"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64495","Department for Education","false","2014-07-10","<p>Our guidance to schools on school uniform is clear that schools must have full regard to their obligations under equalities law, and act reasonably, fairly and flexibly in the interests of all their students.</p><p> </p><p>A school that required compulsory religious items as part of its policy may be at risk of breaching the Equality Act 2010; we would expect all schools to act flexibly in response to reasonable requests to vary their uniform policy.</p><p> </p><p>The Department's guidance on school uniform is available online: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-uniform" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-uniform</a>.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-07-10T16:39:56.8652074Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64495/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64495/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64495/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-27","Schools: Uniforms","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, under what circumstances schools are permitted to require religious headcoverings or other religious items as part of compulsory uniform; and if he will issue revised guidance on this matter to Ofsted.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","202910"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64496","Department for Education","false","2014-07-03","<p>The skills tests for prospective teachers were developed under a contract let by the Training and Development Agency for Schools (TDA) to Pearson VUE in 2009. The Teaching Agency took over responsibility for oversight of contract management in 2012 when the TDA was abolished. Since November 2013, responsibility has rested with the Standards and Testing Agency, an executive agency of the Department for Education.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-07-03T16:56:14.9505123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64496/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64496/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64496/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-27","Pearson VUE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which office in his Department or its arms length bodies has responsibility for the oversight of outsourcing QTS numeracy and skills tests to Pearson VUE.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","202964"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64497","Department for Education","false","2014-07-07","<p>There have been representations made by individuals and candidates regarding Pearson VUE's delivery of the skills tests. These representations have been in relation to technical issues encountered by candidates at the time of sitting the test and requests for appeals where candidates feel there have been exceptional circumstances which should result in another attempt at the test in question being permitted. All representations of this nature are fully investigated by the Standards and Testing Agency.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-07-07T11:47:51.1191255Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64497/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64497/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64497/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-27","Pearson VUE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what representations he has received regarding Pearson VUE's delivery of QTS numeracy and skills tests.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","202962"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64498","Department for Education","false","2014-07-03","<p>Pearson VUE operates a skills test helpline through which candidates' queries and complaints are managed. There is no appeals process against test results.</p><p> </p><p>If a candidate considers that there was a technical or administrative error with the delivery of the test or marking, they are able to raise this either at the test centre at the time of the test or subsequently via the skills test helpline.</p><p> </p><p>All such requests are considered on a case-by-case basis by Pearson VUE. Where appropriate, Pearson VUE escalates appeals to the Standards and Testing Agency to make the final determination.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-07-03T16:51:45.1467859Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64498/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64498/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64498/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-27","Pearson VUE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what Pearson VUE's process is for appealing test results and complaints procedure.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","202963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64499","Department for Education","false","2014-07-03","<p>As the current contractor delivering the skills test for prospective teachers, Pearson VUE reports weekly to officials on day-to-day delivery against agreed service levels. Pearson VUE is also appropriately engaged in handover of the service to the new contractor.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-07-03T16:54:06.0411087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64499/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64499/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64499/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-27","Pearson VUE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if he will make an assessment of the performance of Pearson VUE in delivering skills tests for prospective teachers on behalf of his Department.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","202961"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64500","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-07-02","<p>In January this year, we published a preliminary report on the Renewable Heat Premium Payment (RHPP) heat pump metering programme. This is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/276612/Preliminary_Report_on_the_RHPP_metering_programme_2014-01-31.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/276612/Preliminary_Report_on_the_RHPP_metering_programme_2014-01-31.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p>This report, presents data from more than 400 heat pumps installed in domestic properties on a trial basis.</p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-07-02T13:19:56.7966266Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64500/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64500/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64500/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-27","Renewable Energy: Heating","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if he will provide information on the performance of those heat pumps which have been installed in domestic premises on a trial basis.","false","Biography information for Graham Stringer","Blackley and Broughton","Graham Stringer","202960"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64501","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-07-02","<p>My rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State did not share the views of my rt. hon. Friend the Minister for the Cabinet Office on this issue.</p><p>He also noted advice from the Department that the Department is charged a fixed cost for payroll services based on the number of employees, so there would be no immediate cost saving to the taxpayer in removing the check-off agreement.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-07-02T15:44:59.3459957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64501/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64501/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64501/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-27","Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, for what reasons he decided against change following his review into his Department's check-off system for employees' trade union subscriptions.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","202858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64502","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-07-01","<p>The last year of the Warm Front Scheme was 2012-13. There has been no further change in the Warm Front figures for York local authority area since my answer to you on 9<sup>th</sup> July 2013.</p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker","202846","2014-07-01T16:37:50.5800739Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64502/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64502/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64502/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-27","Warm Front Scheme: York","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how much his Department has spent on the Warm Front scheme in York local authority area in each year since the inception of that scheme.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","202847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64503","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-07-01","<p>The last year of the Warm Front Scheme was 2012-13. There has been no further change in the Warm Front figures for York local authority area since my answer to you on 9<sup>th</sup> July 2013.</p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker","202847","2014-07-01T16:37:49.7676314Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64503/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64503/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64503/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-27","Warm Front Scheme: York","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many (a) single-pensioner households in York and (b) two-pensioner households in York have received Warm Front assistance in each year since the inception of that scheme; and what the average spend has been on each such household.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","202846"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64504","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-07-03","<p> </p><p>The proportion of household waste collected in City of York which was recycled for the five years since 2008/9 is presented in the table below:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Percentage <br> (Rounded)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008/9</p></td><td><p>45%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>43%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>45%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>46%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>46%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The proportion of all waste collected by City of York Council (household and non-household) which was recycled for the five years since 2008/9 is as follows:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Percentage<br> (Rounded)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008/09</p></td><td><p>44%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>42%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>44%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>46%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>45%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>These statistics are taken from data submitted by the Council.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Local authorities receive revenue support grant and council tax to fund waste collection and disposal. These funds are not ring-fenced. We have no record of funding to York City Council specifically to increase recycling rates over this period.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-07-03T10:53:37.233289Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64504/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64504/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/64504/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-27","Recycling: York","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of waste collected in City of York has been recycled in each year since 2008-09; and what funding his Department provided to City of York local authority to increase recycling rates in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","202848"
